Known Issues / Bugs

* Model file dependency issue
  The application depends on exact `.pkl` file names. Any mismatch in file names or missing files results in a runtime error (FileNotFoundError).

* No error handling for model loading
  The app directly loads models using `pickle.load()` without try-except blocks. If a file is missing or corrupted, the app crashes instead of showing a user-friendly message.

* No validation for missing (NaN) values in bulk upload
  Although instructions mention “No NaN values allowed”, the code does not validate or handle missing values, which may lead to incorrect predictions or runtime errors.

* Inefficient model loading (performance issue)
  Models are loaded every time the user clicks the submit button, increasing response time and reducing performance.

* Lack of input validation (manual prediction)
  Users can enter unrealistic or invalid values (e.g., blood pressure = 0), which can affect prediction accuracy and reliability.

* Column order dependency in bulk prediction
  The prediction logic relies on column order (`iloc`) instead of column names. Any change in column order can lead to incorrect predictions.

* Case-sensitive file handling issue
  Deployment environments (like Streamlit Cloud) are case-sensitive. Incorrect capitalization in file names can break the application.

* Duplicate files in repository
  Multiple `app.py` files or unnecessary files (e.g., unused HTML files) can cause confusion and deployment issues.

* No file type validation for upload
  The app allows CSV upload but does not strictly validate file content or structure beyond column names.

* No user feedback for invalid inputs
  The app does not provide clear error messages when users input incorrect or out-of-range values.

* Visualization tab dependency issue
  If `plotly` is not installed, the app fails instead of handling the error gracefully.

* No scalability handling for large datasets
  Uploading large CSV files may slow down or crash the app due to lack of optimization.
